  <!-- ============ METHOD ============ -->
  <section class="method" aria-label="How I build">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="pull">“I build with <b>AI agents</b> the way earlier generations used IDEs — agents wrapped in tests, guardrails, and a human who reads every diff.”</p>
      <div class="method-grid">
        <div class="m-item"><span class="no">01</span><h3>Agents in the loop</h3><p>Cursor and Claude Code as daily drivers — scaffolding, refactors, first-pass reviews.</p></div>
        <div class="m-item"><span class="no">02</span><h3>Tests before trust</h3><p>TDD by default. AI maintains coverage; humans decide what “correct” means.</p></div>
        <div class="m-item"><span class="no">03</span><h3>Tools worth shipping</h3><p><a href="https://pub.dev/packages/graphql_network_devtools" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">graphql_network_devtools</a> on pub.dev; Mason templates that erase boilerplate.</p></div>
        <div class="m-item"><span class="no">04</span><h3>Compounding learning</h3><p>An agent that distils PR-review history into shared team practice.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
